The paper deals with the complexity of a graph problem, specifically the Directed Steiner Network problem, which is a well-studied problem in graph theory and optimization. The paper provides a complete characterization of the classes of directed graphs that result in fixed-parameter tractable special cases of the problem, which suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with graph algorithms, discrete mathematics, computational geometry, graph theory, and complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
